The Fortnite Island has been flipped and a new one has been revealed.

Due to a particularly cold winter, the first thing youâ€™ll notice about the Island is that the western halfâ€™s a wintry biome. Perhaps stop by the suburban Greasy Grove, the industrial Logjam Lumberyard, and other locales.
Like warmer weather? To the east are the tropics, with coastal keys, palm trees, and weathered sights to see. Although The Seven have outposts all throughout the Island, the tropics are home to their home, the â€œSanctuary.â€ This compound is right next to the coast, where you can get a clear view of the colossal rock statue of The Foundation. And speaking of colossal, the towering, web-covered Daily Bugle building is also in the area.
Like even warmer weather? In the south you can find the desert (some of it decorated in snow), but this desert isnâ€™t barren on interesting places. Go off-road racing at Chonkerâ€™s Speedway, revel in cozy living at Condo Canyon, and something that will wet even the driest eyes, â€œcome on downâ€ to the returning Butter Barn. 
A fresh slate of weapons awaits you on the Island. Hereâ€™s a rundown of whatâ€™s new!

Ranger Assault Rifle

Made for distance! The Ranger Assault Rifle is forceful at medium range and quite capable at long range. 

MK-Seven Assault Rifle
Built from The Sevenâ€™s technology, the MK-Seven Assault Rifle is a medium- to long-range weapon with a high rate of fire. This Assault Rifle has a sight you can use while aiming. Align your target with the sightâ€™s red dot!
If you want something even better, confront The Foundation for a special version of the MK-Seven Assault Rifle, sporting a slightly faster fire rate.

The Striker Pump Shotgun shoots a whole lot of pellets and boasts high burst damage. Aimâ€¦ then strike!

An automatic ally that lays down some serious firepower. The Auto Shotgun may not deal as much damage as the Striker Pump per shot, but it has a faster fire rate and reloads two shells at a time.

Appropriately named, the Stinger SMG deals high damage to both opponents and structures. It stings at medium range more than one may expect!
